<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n43093c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n43" href="#n43093c">N43 (VI.B.35)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n43all.htm#n43093c"> 93(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> fanned by / bible leaves</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Belief in the power of the spoken word, notably as a curse, has world-wide illustration; and not less is the power of the written word or of the pictoral symbol. (&hellip;) not so many years back (indeed so persistent are superstitions that kindred practices obtain throughout Europe to this day) sick folk in the Highlands were fanned with the leaves of the Bible. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECSA2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECSA2"><cite title="source">The Story of the Alphabet</cite></a>, rev. ed. (1913) 19 [Introductory]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
